    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1899-09-08T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1899-09-08T00:00:00-05:00" n="771"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d771">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Adee</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Russell</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1899-09-08">
                            <hi rend="italic">September 8, 1899</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 287.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I append hereto translation of telegrams<note
                        n="1" xml:id="d771fn1">Printed ante, <ref target="#pg_793">p.
                        793</ref>.</note> from and to you with regard to the revolution in
                    Venezuela. A naval vessel will be sent to watch events. The news caused much
                    apprehension in business circles here, the gravity of the situation not being
                    confirmed by press or private information.</p>
                <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Alvey A. Adee</hi>,<lb/>
                        <hi rend="italic">Acting Secretary.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
